## ðŸ§­ Lessons Learned

* **Red teams must model not only malicious users, but flawed incentive systems.**
* AI safety depends on simulating **real-world chaos**, not just lab conditions.
* Itâ€™s critical to test how **external platform dynamics** (like Xâ€™s algorithm) affect model outputs.
* Trust in AI is lost fast â€” safety work must be **preventive**Â rather then reactive.

